        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 27 at 8:18AM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>The combination of recent dry weather, relative humidity falling
to 15 to 25 percent, and west to northwesterly winds gusting to 15
mph will result in an elevated threat for the rapid spread of
fires this afternoon into early evening.

Please refer to your local burn permitting authorities on whether
you may burn outdoors. If you do burn, use extreme caution since
fires can quickly grow out of control under these conditions.
</description>
